Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of pushdown systems in software verification, which falls under the category of formal methods. The saturation technique presented in the paper is a method for solving reachability problems in pushdown systems, which is a topic in the area of logic and verification (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of automata-theoretic approach to software model checking, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL). The paper discusses the implementation of scalable model checkers for pushdown systems, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also mentions the analysis of two-player games played over the configuration graph of a pushdown system, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS).
